nl.tno.stormcv.model

Class VideoChunk

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tno.stormcv.model.CVParticle
      • nl.tno.stormcv.model.VideoChunk
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<CVParticle>

    public class VideoChunk
extends CVParticle
    Represents a piece of video containing a number of encoded frames. The FramesToVideoOp and VideoToFramesOp operations can be used to convert a bunch of Frame's into a VideoChunk and the other way around. Videochunks can be used to minimize bandwidth usage compared to sending raw frames. Encoding and decoding of the video however uses more computational power.
    Author:
    Corne Versloot
